                     <p>
                        <seg type="docType">Bargain and sale.</seg>
                        <placeName key="place_116047">Roche Court (Hampshire)</placeName>. <origDate when="1667">19 Chas. II. May 31, 1667</origDate>. Indenture made between (1) Francis Gregg of St Clement Danes, Middlesex,
                        gent.; John Gregg of St Clement Danes, Middlesex, apothecary, and Henry
                        Doble of London, Merchant Taylor; (2) John Thorner of Kings Cleere,
                        Hampshire, esq., and Jane his wife; (3) Sir William Gardiner of London,
                        baronet, and Dame Jane his wife, and (4) Edward Evelyn of Long Ditton,
                        Surrey, esq., Abraham Downing of St Clement Danes, sergeant skinner to His
                        Majesty; Henry Webb of Shidfeild in Bishops Waltham, Hampshire, gent., and
                        Thomas Willoughby of Kings Cleere, Hampshire, gent., being a bargain and
                        sale by (1) to (4) of lands in the manor of North Farham otherwise Roch
                        Court, Hampshire [details given] (endorsed: 'The Lease for 6 months dat.
                        31st May 1667 from [the parties in (1) (2) and (3) to Edward Evelyn
                        [..]).</p>
